  "body": "### What's your issue about?\r\nThe function parameter should be immutable and should not be modified during the function. The direct assignment to a function parameter is forbidden.  However, there is no such check in the Augassign. For example, the following program can compile:\r\n```\r\n@public\r\ndef foo(x:num):\r\n    x += 5     \r\n```\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nIn the stmt.py, add mutability check to function parameters.\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5641590/33234523-ca146bb2-d1ed-11e7-94cb-9005aa316e05.png)\r\n\r\n",
